<MELItem itemNbr="31-51-04" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-31-51-04.1.2-31-51-04">
<Title>Nose Gear Pressure Transducer System</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="1" nbrRequired="0" opsIndicator="(O)">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>May be inoperative provided stabilizer trim position is verified to be properly set before each departure.</Para>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<OperationProcedure>
<Para>Verify the stabilizer trim position is correct for the takeoff thrust, takeoff flaps, gross weight, and center of gravity before each departure.</Para>
<Note>
<Para>The STAB GREENBAND advisory message may be displayed.</Para>
</Note>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Confirm the FMC takeoff data has been correctly initialized (takeoff thrust, takeoff flaps, gross weight, and center of gravity).</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Confirm the stabilizer trim is properly set to the position computed for the takeoff thrust, takeoff flaps, gross weight, and center of gravity.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</OperationProcedure>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELItem>
